Not ready to lose the service of their talisman to other teams, the management of TTC Rh√∂nSprudel Fulda-Maberzell has decided to extend the contract of Quadri Aruna for another two-season in the German Bundesliga. Aruna who joined the German club from Sporting in Portugal in 2020 has been outstanding this season being the best performing player in the club for the 2020/2021 Table Tennis Bundesliga (TTBL) season. With four matches to the end of the season, TTC Fulda has managed to escape relegation having won five matches and lost 13 to occupy the 10th place on the 12-team league table. Already, German internationals Fan Bo Meng and Ruwen Filus have been confirmed to remain with the team for next season and in planning ahead, the management of the club has decided to hand Aruna another two-year deal till 2023.